author: The Current
description:
Watch Frank Black perform 'Teenager of the Year' for The Current's 20th Anniversary
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Pixies frontman Black Francis took on his solo moniker Frank Black for a 30th anniversary performance of his 1994 album, 'Teenager of the Year.' Black's 'Teenager of the Year' set was bookended by selections from his 1993 self-titled album.

Frank Black's set was part of night one of The Current’s 20th Anniversary at First Avenue in Minneapolis on Friday, Jan. 24, 2025.

author: The Current
description:
Watch Beach Bunny performing live at First Avenue in Minneapolis
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Chicago pop-punk band Beach Bunny performed during night two of The Current’s 20th Anniversary at First Avenue in Minneapolis on Saturday, Jan. 25, 2025. Led by a joyous Lili Trifilio on vocals and guitar, the group tore through songs from their forthcoming third album, "Tunnel Vision," as well as favorites from their back catalog. The crowd sang loudly along at several points, and took Trifilio’s directions to start a mosh pit in the center of the floor. During “April,” the mainroom floor turned into a sea of lit-up mobile phones.

description:
Watch Lucy Dacus perform "Ankles" live at The Current
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

While in the Twin Cities (Minnesota) for a pair of shows at the Palace Theatre in St. Paul, Lucy Dacus visited The Current to play songs from the new album, "Forever is a Feeling," including "Ankles," above. 

Lucy Dacus’ 2025 album, 'Forever is a Feeling,' is available on @geffenrecords.

Musicians
Lucy Dacus - vocals, guitar
Alan Good Parker - guitar
Sarah Goldstone - piano
Phoenix Rousiamanis - violin
